Title: #ProudShoreMums stand up for their sons after muck-up day controversy
Summary: Mothers have been posting photos on Instagram and Facebook of their children in Shore uniform, adding blue and white hearts to represent the school's colours.

Title: Stabbing attack near former offices of Charlie Hebdo magazine in Paris
Summary: Police responded to an incident near the former offices of a magazine attacked by terrorists during a deadly wave of assaults five years ago.

Title: New Zealand-born police officer shot dead in London police station
Summary: Sergeant Matiu Ratana was shot dead inside the police station by a suspect who was handcuffed at the time, police said.

Title: Two charged over COVID-19 outbreak at US veterans' home that left 76 dead
Summary: The medical director and superintendent of the facility were indicted on charges of criminal neglect in connection to a coronavirus outbreak.

Title: More elite Sydney schools drawn into 'criminal' muck-up day fiasco
Summary: St Aloysius' College and other schools in northern Sydney have become embroiled in a controversy triggered by Shore School year 12s.

Title: Police officer shot dead in south London
Summary: British police officers remain routinely unarmed, and a survey in 2017 suggested most did not want to carry weapons regularly.

Title: Sydney photographer arrested following sexual assault allegations
Summary: Garth Knight was arrested at his Waterloo home after two women accused him of assaulting them during photo shoots.

Title: Man charged with attack on police found dead in prison cell
Summary: Frederick Fadi Elrezz had been in custody since September 2, when he allegedly attacked a group of three police officers in Sydney's CBD, slashing one in the head and shoulder with a knife.

Title: Relic of Pope John Paul II's blood stolen from Italian cathedral
Summary: The relic was in the Spoleto cathedral temporarily and was due to be moved next month to a new church in Umbria named after the saint and late pope.

Title: Three more charged over Surfers Paradise stabbing death
Summary: Raymond Harris, 27, was stabbed in the torso with a hunting knife on Wednesday and died shortly after in hospital.
